CRDB Bank has recommended a dividend increase by 60 per cent per share to be endorsed by the annual general meeting mid next month. The proposal is an increase from 5/- paid in 2017 to 8/- in 2018 after posting a soaring net profit by 78 per cent. The largest lender in country said in a statement today that subject to approval by the AGM the share will trade cum-dividend from 12 April 2019 and membership register close May 10, 2019.